00027     ROSE_ASSERT(fhdr!=NULL);
00028 
00029     /* Allocate worst-case size for results */
00030     size_t worst_size = (4+
00031                          1+
00032                          get_augmentation_string().size()+1+
00033                          10+
00034                          10+
00035                          10+
00036                          get_augmentation_data_length()+
00037                          get_instructions().size()+
00038                          fhdr->get_word_size());
00039     unsigned char *buf = new unsigned char[worst_size];
00040 
00041     rose_addr_t at = 0;
00042     uint32_t u32_disk;
00043     unsigned char u8_disk;
00044 
00045     /* CIE back offset (always zero) */
00046     u32_disk=0;
00047     memcpy(buf+at, &u32_disk, 4); at+=4;
00048 
00049     /* Version */
00050     u8_disk = get_version();
00051     memcpy(buf+at, &u8_disk, 1); at+=1;
00052 
00053     /* NUL-terminated Augmentation String */
00054     size_t sz = get_augmentation_string().size()+1;
00055     memcpy(buf+at, get_augmentation_string().c_str(), sz); at+=sz;
00056 
00057     /* Alignment factors */
00058     at = ehframe->write_uleb128(buf, at, get_code_alignment_factor());
00059     at = ehframe->write_sleb128(buf, at, get_data_alignment_factor());
00060 
00061     /* Augmentation data */
00062     at = ehframe->write_uleb128(buf, at, get_augmentation_data_length());
00063     std::string astr = get_augmentation_string();
00064     if (!astr.empty() && astr[0]=='z') {
00065         for (size_t i=1; i<astr.size(); i++) {
00066             if ('L'==astr[i]) {
00067                 u8_disk = get_lsda_encoding();
00068                 buf[at++] = u8_disk;
00069             } else if ('P'==astr[i]) {
00070                 u8_disk = get_prh_encoding();
00071                 buf[at++] = u8_disk;
00072                 switch (get_prh_encoding()) {
00073                     case 0x05:
00074                     case 0x06:
00075                     case 0x07:
00076                         buf[at++] = get_prh_arg();
00077                         host_to_le(get_prh_addr(), &u32_disk);
00078                         memcpy(buf+at, &u32_disk, 4); at+=4;
00079                         break;
00080                     default:
00081                         /* See parser */
00082                         if (++nwarnings<=WARNING_LIMIT) {
00083                             fprintf(stderr, "%s:%u: warning: unknown PRH encoding (0x%02x)\n",
00084                                     __FILE__, __LINE__, get_prh_encoding());
00085                             if (WARNING_LIMIT==nwarnings)
00086                                 fprintf(stderr, "    (additional frame warnings will be suppressed)\n");
00087                         }
00088                         break;
00089                 }
00090             } else if ('R'==astr[i]) {
00091                 u8_disk = get_addr_encoding();
00092                 buf[at++] = u8_disk;
00093             } else if ('S'==astr[i]) {
00094                 /* Signal frame; no auxilliary data */
00095             } else {
00096                 ROSE_ASSERT(!"invalid .eh_frame augmentation string");
00097                 abort();
00098             }
00099         }
00100     }
00101 
00102     /* Initial instructions */
00103     sz = get_instructions().size();
00104     if (sz>0) {
00105         memcpy(buf+at, &(get_instructions()[0]), sz);
00106         at += sz;
00107     }
00108 
00109     std::string retval((char*)buf, at);
00110     delete[] buf;
00111     return retval;
00112 }

00167 {
00168     SgAsmElfFileHeader *fhdr = ehframe->get_elf_header();
00169     ROSE_ASSERT(fhdr!=NULL);
00170 
00171     /* Allocate worst-case size for results */
00172     size_t worst_size = 8 + get_augmentation_data().size() + get_instructions().size() + fhdr->get_word_size();
00173     unsigned char *buf = new unsigned char[worst_size];
00174 
00175     size_t sz;
00176     rose_addr_t at = 0;
00177     uint32_t u32_disk;
00178 
00179     /* PC Begin (begin_rva) and size */
00180     switch (cie->get_addr_encoding()) {
00181         case -1:          /* No address encoding specified */
00182         case 0x01:
00183         case 0x03:
00184         case 0x1b: {
00185             host_to_le(get_begin_rva().get_rva(), &u32_disk);
00186             memcpy(buf+at, &u32_disk, 4); at+=4;
00187             host_to_le(get_size(), &u32_disk);
00188             memcpy(buf+at, &u32_disk, 4); at+=4;
00189             break;
00190         }
00191         default:
00192             /* See parser */
00193             if (++nwarnings<=WARNING_LIMIT) {
00194                 fprintf(stderr, "%s:%u: warning: unknown FDE address encoding (0x%02x)\n",
00195                         __FILE__, __LINE__, cie->get_addr_encoding());
00196                 if (WARNING_LIMIT==nwarnings)
00197                     fprintf(stderr, "    (additional frame warnings will be suppressed)\n");
00198             }
00199             break;
00200     }
00201 
00202     /* Augmentation Data */
00203     std::string astr = cie->get_augmentation_string();
00204     if (astr.size()>0 && astr[0]=='z') {
00205         at = ehframe->write_uleb128(buf, at, get_augmentation_data().size());
00206         sz = get_augmentation_data().size();
00207         if (sz>0) {
00208             memcpy(buf+at, &(get_augmentation_data()[0]), sz);
00209             at += sz;
00210         }
00211     }
00212 
00213     /* Call frame instructions */
00214     sz = get_instructions().size();
00215     if (sz>0) {
00216         memcpy(buf+at, &(get_instructions()[0]), sz);
00217         at += sz;
00218     }

00221     delete[] buf;

00257 SgAsmElfEHFrameSection *
00258 SgAsmElfEHFrameSection::parse()
00259 {
00260     SgAsmElfSection::parse();
00261     SgAsmElfFileHeader *fhdr = get_elf_header();
00262     ROSE_ASSERT(fhdr!=NULL);
00263 
00264     rose_addr_t record_offset=0;
00265     std::map<rose_addr_t, SgAsmElfEHFrameEntryCI*> cies;
00266 
00267     while (record_offset<get_size()) {
00268         rose_addr_t at = record_offset;
00269         unsigned char u8_disk;
00270         uint32_t u32_disk;
00271         uint64_t u64_disk;
00272 
00273         /* Length or extended length */
00274         rose_addr_t length_field_size = 4; /*number of bytes not counted in length*/
00275         read_content_local(at, &u32_disk, 4); at += 4;
00276         rose_addr_t record_size = disk_to_host(fhdr->get_sex(), u32_disk);
00277         if (record_size==0xffffffff) {
00278             read_content_local(at, &u64_disk, 8); at += 8;
00279             record_size = disk_to_host(fhdr->get_sex(), u64_disk);
00280             length_field_size += 8; /*FIXME: it's not entirely clear whether ExtendedLength includes this field*/
00281         }
00282         if (0==record_size)
00283             break;
00284 
00285         /* Backward offset to CIE record, or zero if this is a CIE record. */
00286         read_content_local(at, &u32_disk, 4); at += 4;
00287         rose_addr_t cie_back_offset = disk_to_host(fhdr->get_sex(), u32_disk);
00288         if (0==cie_back_offset) {
00289             /* This is a CIE record */
00290             SgAsmElfEHFrameEntryCI *cie = new SgAsmElfEHFrameEntryCI(this);
00291             cies[record_offset] = cie;
00292 
00293             /* Version */
00294             uint8_t cie_version;
00295             read_content_local(at++, &cie_version, 1);
00296             cie->set_version(cie_version);
00297 
00298             /* Augmentation String */
00299             std::string astr = read_content_local_str(at);
00300             at += astr.size() + 1;
00301             cie->set_augmentation_string(astr);
00302 
00303             /* Alignment factors */
00304             cie->set_code_alignment_factor(read_content_local_uleb128(&at));
00305             cie->set_data_alignment_factor(read_content_local_sleb128(&at));
00306 
00307             /* Augmentation data length. This is apparently the length of the data described by the Augmentation String plus
00308              * the Initial Instructions plus any padding. [RPM 2009-01-15] */
00309             cie->set_augmentation_data_length(read_content_local_uleb128(&at));
00310 
00311             /* Augmentation data. The format of the augmentation data in the CIE record is determined by reading the
00312              * characters of the augmentation string. */ 
00313             if (!astr.empty() && astr[0]=='z') {
00314                 for (size_t i=1; i<astr.size(); i++) {
00315                     if ('L'==astr[i]) {
00316                         read_content_local(at++, &u8_disk, 1);
00317                         cie->set_lsda_encoding(u8_disk);
00318                     } else if ('P'==astr[i]) {
00319                         /* The first byte is an encoding method which describes the following bytes, which are the address of
00320                          * a Personality Routine Handler. There appears to be very little documentation about these fields. */
00321                         read_content_local(at++, &u8_disk, 1);
00322                         cie->set_prh_encoding(u8_disk);
00323                         switch (cie->get_prh_encoding()) {
00324                             case 0x05:          /* See Ubuntu 32bit /usr/bin/aptitude */
00325                             case 0x06:          /* See second CIE record for Gentoo-Amd64 /usr/bin/addftinfo */
00326                             case 0x07:          /* See first CIE record for Gentoo-Amd64 /usr/bin/addftinfo */
00327                                 read_content_local(at++, &u8_disk, 1); /* not sure what this is; arg for __gxx_personality_v0? */
00328                                 cie->set_prh_arg(u8_disk);
00329                                 read_content_local(at, &u32_disk, 4); at+=4; /* address of <__gxx_personality_v0@plt> */
00330                                 cie->set_prh_addr(le_to_host(u32_disk));
00331                                 break;
00332                             case 0x09:          /* *.o file generated by gcc-4.0.x */
00333                                 /* FIXME: Cannot find any info about this entry. Fix SgAsmElfEHFrameSection::parse() if we
00334                                  *        ever figure this out. [RPM 2009-09-29] */
00335                                 /*fallthrough*/
00336                             default: {
00337                                 if (++nwarnings<=WARNING_LIMIT) {
00338                                     fprintf(stderr, "%s:%u: warning: ELF CIE 0x%08"PRIx64" has unknown PRH encoding 0x%02x\n", 
00339                                             __FILE__, __LINE__, get_offset()+record_offset, cie->get_prh_encoding());
00340                                     if (WARNING_LIMIT==nwarnings)
00341                                         fprintf(stderr, "    (additional frame warnings will be suppressed)\n");
00342                                 }
00343                                 break;
00344                             }
00345                         }
00346                     } else if ('R'==astr[i]) {
00347                         read_content_local(at++, &u8_disk, 1);
00348                         cie->set_addr_encoding(u8_disk);
00349                     } else if ('S'==astr[i]) {
00350                         /* See http://lkml.indiana.edu/hypermail/linux/kernel/0602.3/1144.html and GCC PR #26208*/
00351                         cie->set_sig_frame(true);
00352                     } else {
00353                         /* Some stuff we don't handle yet. Warn about it and don't read anything. */
00354                         if (++nwarnings<=WARNING_LIMIT) {
00355                             fprintf(stderr, "%s:%u: warning: ELF CIE 0x%08"PRIx64" has invalid augmentation string \"%s\"\n", 
00356                                     __FILE__, __LINE__, get_offset()+record_offset, escapeString(astr).c_str());
00357                             if (WARNING_LIMIT==nwarnings)
00358                                 fprintf(stderr, "    (additional frame warnings will be suppressed)\n");
00359                         }
00360                     }
00361                 }
00362             }
00363 
00364             /* Initial instructions. These are apparently included in the augmentation_data_length. The final instructions can
00365              * be zero padding (no-op instructions) to bring the record up to a multiple of the word size. */
00366             rose_addr_t init_insn_size = (length_field_size + record_size) - (at - record_offset);
00367             cie->get_instructions() = read_content_local_ucl(at, init_insn_size);
00368             ROSE_ASSERT(cie->get_instructions().size()==init_insn_size);
00369 
00370         } else {
00371             /* This is a FDE record */
00372             rose_addr_t cie_offset = record_offset + length_field_size - cie_back_offset;
00373             assert(cies.find(cie_offset)!=cies.end());
00374             SgAsmElfEHFrameEntryCI *cie = cies[cie_offset];
00375             SgAsmElfEHFrameEntryFD *fde = new SgAsmElfEHFrameEntryFD(cie);
00376 
00377             /* PC Begin (begin_rva) and size */
00378             switch (cie->get_addr_encoding()) {
00379               case -1:          /* No address encoding specified */
00380               case 0x01:
00381               case 0x03:
00382               case 0x1b:        /* Address doesn't look valid (e.g., 0xfffd74e8) but still four bytes [RPM 2008-01-16]*/
00383               {
00384                   read_content_local(at, &u32_disk, 4); at+=4;
00385                   fde->set_begin_rva(le_to_host(u32_disk));
00386                   read_content_local(at, &u32_disk, 4); at+=4;
00387                   fde->set_size(le_to_host(u32_disk));
00388                   break;
00389               }
00390               default:
00391                 fprintf(stderr, "%s:%u: ELF CIE 0x%08"PRIx64", FDE 0x%08"PRIx64": unknown address encoding: 0x%02x\n", 
00392                         __FILE__, __LINE__, get_offset()+cie_offset, get_offset()+record_offset, cie->get_addr_encoding());
00393                 abort();
00394             }
00395 
00396             /* Augmentation Data */
00397             std::string astring = cie->get_augmentation_string();
00398             if (astring.size()>0 && astring[0]=='z') {
00399                 rose_addr_t aug_length = read_content_local_uleb128(&at);
00400                 fde->get_augmentation_data() = read_content_local_ucl(at, aug_length);
00401                 at += aug_length;
00402                 ROSE_ASSERT(fde->get_augmentation_data().size()==aug_length);
00403             }
00404 
00405             /* Call frame instructions */
00406             rose_addr_t cf_insn_size = (length_field_size + record_size) - (at - record_offset);
00407             fde->get_instructions() = read_content_local_ucl(at, cf_insn_size);
00408             ROSE_ASSERT(fde->get_instructions().size()==cf_insn_size);
00409         }
00410 
00411         record_offset += length_field_size + record_size;
00412     }
00413     return this;
00414 }

00443 rose_addr_t
00444 SgAsmElfEHFrameSection::unparse(std::ostream *fp) const
00445 {
00446     SgAsmElfFileHeader *fhdr = get_elf_header();
00447     ROSE_ASSERT(fhdr!=NULL);
00448 
00449     rose_addr_t at=0;
00450     uint32_t u32_disk;
00451     uint64_t u64_disk;
00452 
00453     for (size_t i=0; i<get_ci_entries()->get_entries().size(); i++) {
00454         rose_addr_t last_cie_offset = at;
00455         SgAsmElfEHFrameEntryCI *cie = get_ci_entries()->get_entries()[i];
00456         std::string s = cie->unparse(this);
00457         if (s.size()<0xffffffff) {
00458             host_to_disk(fhdr->get_sex(), s.size(), &u32_disk);
00459             if (fp)
00460                 write(*fp, at, 4, &u32_disk);
00461             at += 4;
00462         } else {
00463             u32_disk = 0xffffffff;
00464             if (fp)
00465                 write(*fp, at, 4, &u32_disk);
00466             at += 4;
00467             host_to_disk(fhdr->get_sex(), s.size(), &u64_disk);
00468             if (fp)
00469                 write(*fp, at, 8, &u64_disk);
00470             at += 8;
00471         }
00472         if (fp)
00473             write(*fp, at, s);
00474         at += s.size();
00475 
00476         for (size_t j=0; j<cie->get_fd_entries()->get_entries().size(); j++) {
00477             SgAsmElfEHFrameEntryFD *fde = cie->get_fd_entries()->get_entries()[j];
00478             std::string s = fde->unparse(this, cie);
00479 
00480             /* Record size, not counting run-length coded size field, but counting CIE back offset. */
00481             rose_addr_t record_size = 4 + s.size();
00482             if (record_size<0xffffffff) {
00483                 host_to_disk(fhdr->get_sex(), record_size, &u32_disk);
00484                 if (fp)
00485                     write(*fp, at, 4, &u32_disk);
00486                 at += 4;
00487             } else {
00488                 u32_disk = 0xffffffff;
00489                 if (fp)
00490                     write(*fp, at, 4, &u32_disk);
00491                 at += 4;
00492                 host_to_disk(fhdr->get_sex(), record_size, &u64_disk);
00493                 if (fp)
00494                     write(*fp, at, 8, &u64_disk);
00495                 at += 8;
00496             }
00497 
00498             /* CIE back offset. Number of bytes from the beginning of the current CIE record (including the Size fields) to
00499              * the beginning of the FDE record (excluding the Size fields but including the CIE back offset). */
00500             rose_addr_t cie_back_offset = at - last_cie_offset;
00501             host_to_disk(fhdr->get_sex(), cie_back_offset, &u32_disk);
00502             if (fp)
00503                 write(*fp, at, 4, &u32_disk);
00504             at += 4;
00505 
00506             /* The FDE record itself */
00507             if (fp)
00508                 write(*fp, at, s);
00509             at += s.size();
00510         }
00511     }
